Optimization
\series default
: Use the Lagrangian method to solve for Lisa's optimal choices of 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $l$
\end_inset

 before and after reform.
 You can reduce the problem to 
\begin_inset Formula $3$
\end_inset

 variables but not less than that.
 Given the utility function, you are asked to use, all the optimal quantities
 will be positive.
 Call the optimal values of this situation 1: 
\begin_inset Formula $c^{1},L^{1},m^{1},\theta^{1},l^{1}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Answer:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.1.
 
\begin_inset Formula $pc+w(m+L)\leq wT$
\end_inset

, the utility 
\begin_inset Formula $U(c,L,\theta)=c^{a}+L^{a}+\theta^{a}$
\end_inset

 it s a CES utility function it is concave for 
\begin_inset Formula $a\leq1$
\end_inset

 and and convex for 
\begin_inset Formula $a>1$
\end_inset

, it is monotone as it increases its value with positive quantities of consumpti
on of 
\begin_inset Formula $c,L,\theta$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.2.
 I write down the problem in terms of 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 replacing the equation 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=bm$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{L}(c,L,m)=c^{a}+L^{a}+(bm)^{a}+(wT-pc-w(m+L))$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We proceed to obtain the derivatives of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{L}$
\end_inset

 with respect to 
\begin_inset Formula $c,L,m$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial\mathcal{L}}{\partial c}=ac^{-1+a}-p\lambda=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial\mathcal{L}}{\partial L}=aL^{-1+a}-w\lambda=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial\mathcal{L}}{\partial m}=ab(bm)^{-1+a}-w\lambda=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial\mathcal{L}}{\partial\lambda}=wT-pc-w(m+L)=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now, we proceed to find optimal values of 
\begin_inset Formula $c,L,m$
\end_inset

 in terms of the parameters of the problem, t his is done by solving the
 system of equatios implied by the FOC of the Lagrangian.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this particular case, echoing what we have done in class, we write down
 two MRS conditions the first MRS
\begin_inset Formula $(L,c)$
\end_inset

 and MRS
\begin_inset Formula $(m,c)$
\end_inset

, then use that to obtain 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 in terms of 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 and parameters, and 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 in terms of 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 and parameters.
 Then we replace back in the budget constraint to obtain the optimal value
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 in terms of parameters alone and then solve the whole problem.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The two MRS conditions are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
c^{-1+a}L^{1-a}=\frac{p}{w}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
c^{-1+a}m(bm)^{-a}=\frac{p}{w}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From this I obtain:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
L=c\left(\frac{p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
m=c\left(\frac{b^{a}p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then replace in the budget constraint:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Tw-c\left(p+\left(\left(\frac{p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}+\left(\frac{b^{a}p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}\right)w\right)=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Obtain the optimal quantities, as you can see LHS is full of parameters
 and no variable remains, also I have verified that this quantities satisfy
 the budget contraint:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
c^{*1}=\frac{Tw}{p+\left(\left(\frac{p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}+\left(\frac{b^{a}p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}\right)w}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
L^{*1}=\frac{Tw\left(\frac{p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}}{p+\left(\left(\frac{p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}+\left(\frac{b^{a}p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}\right)w}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
m^{*1}=\frac{Tw}{w+\left(\frac{b^{a}p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{-1+a}}\left(p+\left(\frac{p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}w\right)}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\theta^{*1}=b\frac{Tw}{w+\left(\frac{b^{a}p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{-1+a}}\left(p+\left(\frac{p}{w}\right)^{\frac{1}{1-a}}w\right)}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

